quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,67,"And [recall] when Moses said to his people, "
  2,68,"They said, "
  2,69,"They said, "
  3,7,"It is He who has sent down to you, [O Muḥammad], the Book; in it are verses [that are] precise - they are the foundation of the Book - and others unspecific.{1} As for those in whose hearts is deviation [from truth], they will follow that of it which is unspecific, seeking discord and seeking an interpretation [suitable to them]. And no one knows its [true] interpretation except Allāh. But those firm in knowledge say, ",1:[Those which are stated in such a way that they are open to more than one interpretation or whose meaning is known only to Allāh, such as the opening letters of certain sūrahs.]
  3,8,"[Who say], ",1:[Who gives and grants continually without being asked.]
  3,9,"Our Lord, surely You will gather the people for a Day about which there is no doubt. Indeed, Allāh does not fail in His promise."